		"description": "<p>At 18th level when you roll a failed death saving throw you may choose instead to enter the mindscape fully. Doing so restores you to full health, though your body remains dead. You become a thoughtform that cannot leave the mindscape, but can communicate with nearby creatures and travel in the mindscape of willing creatures.</p><p>A willing creature can also choose to host your consciousness for up to 1 minute, allowing you to interact with the real world as if you were alive, using their body in a form of possession.</p><p>If and when you are restored to life, your thoughtform returns to your body.</p><p>This ability has no effect if you are killed in the mindscape, and if your thoughtform is killed after your body, you die normally.</p>",
